BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/davis-r-users-group-2026"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:Davis R Users' Group
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T170000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T190000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51754758575047
DESCRIPTION:D-RUG\, our local R Users' Group\, meets weekly to facilitate 
 learning and using the R software language. R users from all domains are i
 nvited to bring their R-specific coding problems and share their experienc
 e with other members of the community. Meetup formats include everything f
 rom group discussion and mini-workshops to coworking sessions. D-RUG is ru
 n by volunteer Coo[R]dinators including UC Davis data scientists and gradu
 ate students dedicated to growing and strengthening the R community.\n\n \
 n\nToday's session is open-forum format to foster a communal\, co-working 
 environment. Come hang out and chat\, work on your own\, seek and give hel
 p\, and make friends.\n\n \n\nD-RUG meets Thursdays in person from 10 AM t
 o 12 PM at the DataLab Classroom (Shields Library room 360) on the UC Davi
 s campus. \n\nSign up for our mailing list to get the most up to date info
 rmation\, including a Zoom link to join us virtually if you can't make it 
 in person. Learn more about D-RUG on our website.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/davis-r-users-group-2026
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/human-x-machine-collaborative-ai-learning-lab"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:Human x Machine: A Collaborative AI Learning Lab for Undergrads
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T170000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T190000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51817792490919
DESCRIPTION:Undergrads are invited to drop into our new AI Learning Lab se
 ssions! Participants will: \n \n\nExperiment safely with various AI tools 
 (ChatGPT\, Claude\, Perplexity\, image generators\, research assistants\, 
 etc.) in a supportive environmentDevelop critical evaluation skills to ass
 ess AI outputs for accuracy\, bias\, and appropriatenessLearn ethical fram
 eworks for integrating AI into academic work while maintaining integritySh
 are discoveries and challenges with peers facing similar questions about A
 I useBuild confidence in making informed decisions about when\, how\, and 
 whether to use AI toolsUnderstand disciplinary differences in AI policies 
 and best practices across fields\n Led by Student Services intern Rayan Ma
 nsoor\, these informal sessions will be held biweekly on Tuesdays through 
 March 10  in Shields Library\, Learning Instruction Room\, Rm. 205.\n\nNo 
 prior experience with AI is necessary. Please bring your own device.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, Library Instruction Rm 205
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/human-x-machine-collaborative
 -ai-learning-lab
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
