SUMMARY:Sip Yolo with Yolo County Wines
DESCRIPTION:Discover the charm of Yolo County’s wine country this season by visiting our Yolo Wines wineries. From cozy tasting rooms to stunning vineyard views\, each tasting room offers award-winning wines\, hometown hospitality\, and wines perfect for gifting.  Gather your friends\, sip something new\, and make this season a little more delicious. \nVisit https://www.yolocountywines.com/events to see holiday winery events and to plan your wine trail! \n@berryessagapvineyards @collinadebella @elevationten @fjordoakwinery @greatbearvineyards @grindstonewines @heringerestates @juliettawinery @matchbookwines @sekahills @siltwineco @taberranch @turkovichwines  \n 
URL:https://visityolo.com/event/sip-yolo-with-yolo-county-wines/2026-03-14/
LOCATION:Yolo County Vineyard and Winery Association\, 13 winery locations!
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visityolo.com/wp-content/uploads/yolo-county-wines.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visityolo Event": "https://visityolo.com/event/art-in-bloom/2026-03-14/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visityolo_event
X-SOURCE:Visityolo Event
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T170000
DTSTAMP:20260310T192928
CREATED:20260223T233247Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260223T233247Z
UID:10013558-1773487800-1773507600@visityolo.com
SUMMARY:Art in Bloom
DESCRIPTION:Art in Bloom \n  \nDates/times: March 13\, 6-9 PM\, March 14-15\, 11:30 AM – 5 PM  \nLocation: Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA 95616 \nAdmission: Admission to the Pence is free; we welcome donations from visitors\, as they help us cover basic costs associated with running a nonprofit art gallery. \n  \nArt in Bloom is the first collaboration with members of the Davis Flower Arrangers and the Pence Gallery\, in which creative floral arrangements are paired with specific artworks on view at the Pence from March 13-15. On Friday\, March 13\, from 6-9 PM\, enjoy meeting many of the participating floral designers and see the arrangements as they are at their freshest\, as part of the city’s 2nd Friday ArtAbout reception. Visitors are welcome to enjoy a variety of arrangements that include traditional and unusual materials\, and a variety of beautiful containers. The connection between the artwork and floral design can include using similar colors\, themes\, textures\, or overall composition.  \n  \nParticipating floral designers include Janet Goehring\, Joyce Hamaguchi\, Elly Fairclough\, MJ Kelly\, Rhody Vallejo\, Elisabetta Vivoda\, Mike MacDonald\, Stephanie DeGraff-Hunt\, and Julie Haney. Each artist has chosen an artwork for inspiration\, and will create a vibrant interpretation of pieces by exhibiting artists Manuel Fernando Rios\, Barbara Prodaniuk\, and artists from Assorted Flavors\, our annual exhibit of artworks created by forty Pence members.  \n  \nFounded in 1958\, the Davis Flower Arrangers is a long-standing organization in Davis\, dedicated to studying and instructing floral design techniques\, including Ikebana. The group\, celebrating its 67th season in 2025-26\, promotes the public appreciation of floral art through workshops\, demonstrations\, and community events. For more information on the Davis Flower Arrangers\, contact President Stephanie DeGraff-Hunt at sdegraffhunt@gmail.com.  \n  \nImage: Davis Flower Arrangement (past event)
URL:https://visityolo.com/event/art-in-bloom/2026-03-14/
LOCATION:Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA 95616
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visityolo.com/wp-content/uploads/Art-in-Bloom-copy.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Pence Gallery":MAILTO:pencesocialmedia@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visityolo Event": "https://visityolo.com/event/beetlejuice-jr/2026-03-14/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visityolo_event
X-SOURCE:Visityolo Event
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T160000
DTSTAMP:20260310T192928
CREATED:20250724T211913Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20250724T211913Z
UID:10010782-1773496800-1773504000@visityolo.com
SUMMARY:Beetlejuice Jr
DESCRIPTION:Beetlejuice Jr – March 14 through April 5\, 2026\nSchool Matinees: March 31\, 2026; 9:15am and noon \n  \nIt’s our show now\, kid. The ghost-with-the-most comes to the stage in Beetlejuice JR.\, the frightfully funny musical based on the beloved motion picture turned Broadway phenomenon. Lydia Deetz is a strange and unusual teenager\, still grieving the loss of her mother and obsessed with the whole “being dead thing.” Lucky for Lydia\, she and her father move to a new house haunted by a recently deceased couple and Beetlejuice\, a delightful demon with a real zest for life. When Lydia calls on Beetlejuice to scare away anyone with a pulse\, this double-crossing specter shows his true stripes\, unleashing a (Nether)world of pandemonium. \nRecommended for ages 10 & up \n  \nDirected by Tea Pusey\nChoreographed by Logan Sexton\nMusical direction by Montana Monce
URL:https://visityolo.com/event/beetlejuice-jr/2026-03-14/
LOCATION:Davis Musical Theatre Company (DMTC)\, The Jean Henderson Performing Arts Center\, 607 Pena Drive\, Davis
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visityolo.com/wp-content/uploads/Beetlejuice-Jr.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Davis Musical Theatre Company (DMTC)":MAILTO:info@dmtc.org
END:VEVENT
