BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/covered-faculty-author-talks-by-lisa-materson-and-corrie-decker"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:Covered: Faculty Author Talks by Lisa G. Materson and Corrie Decke
 r
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T123000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T143000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51817323649794
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with UC Davis faculty authors Lisa G. M
 aterson and Corrie Decker as part of Covered\, a monthly event series cele
 brating recent books from the College of Letters and Science.\n \n\nLisa G
 . Materson\, associate professor of history\, traces civil rights activist
  Ruth Reynolds’ deep involvement in the movement for Puerto Rico’s ind
 ependence in Radical Solidarity\, offering a nuanced account of political 
 allyship\, anti-colonial struggle and cross-racial collaboration. \n Corri
 e Decker\, associate professor of history\, examines how colonial courts a
 nd ethnographers in 20th century East Africa transformed complex rites of 
 passage into simplified “puberty rites" in The Age of Sex: Custom\, Law\
 , and Ritual in Twentieth-Century East Africa\, reshaping legal understand
 ings of childhood\, adulthood\, gender and sexual maturity. \n \n\nCovered
 : Spotlighting Faculty Authors in Letters and Science is co-sponsored by t
 he Jan Shrem and Maria Manetti Shrem Museum and the UC Davis Library.
LOCATION:Manetti Shrem Museum
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/covered-faculty-author-talks-
 by-lisa-materson-and-corrie-decker
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/davis-r-users-group-2026"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:Davis R Users' Group
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T170000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T190000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51754758583243
DESCRIPTION:D-RUG\, our local R Users' Group\, meets weekly to facilitate 
 learning and using the R software language. R users from all domains are i
 nvited to bring their R-specific coding problems and share their experienc
 e with other members of the community. Meetup formats include everything f
 rom group discussion and mini-workshops to coworking sessions. D-RUG is ru
 n by volunteer Coo[R]dinators including UC Davis data scientists and gradu
 ate students dedicated to growing and strengthening the R community.\n\n \
 n\nToday's session is open-forum format to foster a communal\, co-working 
 environment. Come hang out and chat\, work on your own\, seek and give hel
 p\, and make friends.\n\n \n\nD-RUG meets Thursdays in person from 10 AM t
 o 12 PM at the DataLab Classroom (Shields Library room 360) on the UC Davi
 s campus. \n\nSign up for our mailing list to get the most up to date info
 rmation\, including a Zoom link to join us virtually if you can't make it 
 in person. Learn more about D-RUG on our website.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/davis-r-users-group-2026
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
