BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Campusgroups": "https://aggielife.ucdavis.edu/rsvp?id=906592"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_campusgroups
SUMMARY:Grad Fest
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260510T230000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260511T040000Z
UID:bdd04ca0e61cef983039d9076216151011252025_3:53:16_PM@campusgroups.com
DESCRIPTION:Celebratory Grad Fest will be a free campus wide festival open
  to all students\, featuring food\, speakers\, student grad acknowledgment
 \, music and dance performances\, and local vendors/Bazaar. The event prov
 ides a joyful space for this year's graduates to celebrate their achieveme
 nts with classmates\, friends\, and family. Graduates will have the opport
 unity to submit their names for public shout outs during the event\, givin
 g them well deserved recognition. There will also be a photo station\; wit
 h a graduation backdrop\, a "I did it!" Sign\, and Family photo corner.\nW
 e are also planning on having a cap-decorating station. \nThis fest not on
 ly honors individual accomplishments but also highlights the value of educ
 ation and the hard work it takes to earn a degree. This event will blend c
 ulture\, performance\, and social bonding. It centers global awareness by 
 connecting SOF students in Afghanistan with local graduates here. This in 
 turn brings families\, cultures\, and communities together. It promotes cu
 ltural engagement and inclusivity. Educational programming through storyte
 lling\, performers\, community resources\, and cultural vendors. In turn\,
  this will help break down stereotypes and bring people together through s
 hared understanding.\nWhat we're doing with this ceremony is building a br
 idge between communities that usually feel worlds apart. We're creating a 
 moment where students from completely different backgrounds can be celebra
 ted together\, and that shared recognition helps grow understanding\, empa
 thy\, and acceptance. By honoring students from all communities who have a
 chieved success in higher education\, we're also highlighting the importan
 ce of inclusivity\, gender equality\, and the right to education. That mat
 ters even more when we think about the girls in Afghanistan who would give
  anything just to go to school and who were still able to pursue their edu
 cation despite the Taliban trying to stop them. These young women have wor
 ked incredibly hard to graduate\, and hosting a ceremony for them alongsid
 e UC Davis students not only celebrates achievement but shows the power of
  connection\, support\, and global solidarity. It's a reminder that educat
 ion shouldn't be limited by gender or geography\, and that celebrating eac
 h other's success is itself a form of resistance.
URL:https://aggielife.ucdavis.edu/rsvp?id=906592
X-SOURCE:UC Davis CampusGroups
END:VEVENT
